<P>A SERMON PREACHED BEFORE THE HONORABLE COUNCIL, AND THE HONORABLE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES, OF THE STATE of MASSACHUSETTS-BAY, IN NEW-ENGLAND, AT BOSTON, MAY 27, 1778.</P>
<P>BEING THE ANNIVERSARY FOR THE ELECTION OF THE HONORABLE COUNCIL.</P>
<P>By PHILLIPS PAYSON, A. M. PASTOR OF A CHURCH IN CHELSEA.</P>
<P>BOSTON: <HI>N. E.</HI> PRINTED BY JOHN GILL, PRINTER TO THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY. M DCC LXXVIII.</P>
